=== DOCUMENTATION FOR TARGET: SUBCPU_SYS_CFG ===

<target_short_dscr>:
Sub-CPU system settings
------------------------------
<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Configurations for the sub-CPU system.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
General purpose register
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
General purpose 32-bit register for software development and debug.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
General control register
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Use this field to change from Boot mode to Normal mode. In Boot mode, the reset vector of the sub-CPU maps to CS0 on the FLASH interface of the main CPU system. When in Normal mode, this address maps instead to the Code memory.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: The sub-CPU system memory map is in Normal mode.
1: The sub-CPU system memory map is in Boot mode.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Enable subCPU UART interface on GPIOs.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Enable subCPU I2C interface on GPIOs.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Force reset the watchdog timer of the sub-CPU system. Once enabled, the WDT cannot be disabled unless it is reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Soft reset the sub-CPU system. The AMBA fabric and peripherals may be protected through SUBCPU_SYS_CFG:SYSTEM_CTRL:RESET_PROTECT.SOFT_RST_PROT_AMBA.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
General status information
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Debug information for checking register read/write problems. This is a read-only field which can only be cleared by reset of the sub-CPU system.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: No errors detected.
1: Non-32bit access to registers, access has been discarded, read returns 0x8888 or 0x88.
2: reserved
3: reserved
4: Unimplemented sub-CPU system register, access has been discarded, read returns 0x88888888.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Indicates the sleeping status of the sub-CPU.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 : CPU active
1 : CPU sleeping
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Protect reset targets from reset sources
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Protect AMBA and peripherals from WDT timeout reset and any soft reset mapped to the sub-CPU address space.
This includes the SYSTEM_CTRL:RESET.SOFT_RST soft reset.
The watchdog timer of the sub-CPU system is not protected.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Protect watchdog timer from WDT timeout reset and any soft reset mapped to the sub-CPU address space.
This includes the SYSTEM_CTRL:RESET.SOFT_RST soft reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This configuration protects the sub-CPU system from System Reset (Except for ATPG Mode).
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 -  When system reset is asserted, even the sub-CPU system will be reset.
1 -  When system reset is asserted, the sub-CPU system will not be reset.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This configuration protects the sub-CPU from reset due to entering a locked-up state.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Reset-cause register
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Indication that system reset was asserted. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Indication that force reset was asserted. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Indication that soft reset was asserted by the sub-CPU. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Indication that soft reset was asserted through the respective configuration field. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Indication that reset due to lock was asserted. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Indication that WDT reset was asserted. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<reggrp_short_dscr>:
SPI Master Controller
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Enable slave-select forcing
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Use to enable forcing of the slave select of the SPI master controller. When set, the slave select is driven by SUBCPU_SYS_CFG:SS_FORCE. When 0, the slave select is driven by the SPI master, and SUBCPU_SYS_CFG:SS_FORCE must be kept at 1.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Slave select value to force
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Value to drive on the slave select output. This field is used when SUBCPU_SYS_CFG:SS_FORCE_ENA is set to 1. Otherwise it must be kept to 1.
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Set mapping of slave select
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Each bit corresponds to a shared slave-select. Multiple bits may be cleared for broadcasting. The final slave-select mapping depends on the following configurations:

SUBCPU_SYS_CFG:SIMC[0]:SS_MASK.SS_MASK
SUBCPU_SYS_CFG:SIMC[1]:SS_MASK.SS_MASK
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
one-cold encoding
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Master contention configuration.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Hooked up to the master contention input (ss_in_n) of the SPI Master block .
------------------------------
<reggrp_short_dscr>:
TWI hold time configuration
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
TWI hold time configuration
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Configure the hold time delay to apply to SDA after SCK when transmitting from the device. This delay is expressed in a number of VCore System clock cycles. The delay value should be as close to 300ns as possible without going below 300ns.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
Set to (300ns/4.8ns + 2) = 65
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set this field to enable hold time on the TWI SDA output. When enabled the TWI_CONFIG.TWI_CNT_RELOAD field determines the amount of hold time to apply to SDA.
------------------------------
<reggrp_short_dscr>:
TWI spike filter configuration
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
TWI spike filter configuration
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Configuration of the spike filter width on the SCL and SDA inputs.
Filters spikes with a width of (SPIKE_FILTER_CFG+1)*SYSTEM_CLK or less.
------------------------------
